massachusetts democrats pick national convention delegates through a primary-caucus system
all of the state's 98 pledged delegates to the democratic national convention will be allocated among the presidential candidates in proportion to the results of the march 8 primary. the delegates themselves will be chosen at caucuses and meetings in following weeks
former house speaker thomas p. o'neill jr. automatically will be given a seat as an unpledged delegate. o'neill is one of five former democratic party leaders nationwide who receive automatic delegate status
