delegates: 52
delegates allocated: tuesday, march 8
selection of delegates: dates not yet determined
massachusetts republicans allocate their national convention delegates among presidential candidates in proportion to results of the march 8 primary
all candidates receiving at least 1.923 percent of the statewide vote are eligible to receive delegates
allocation of delegates is made by an allocation committee after the primary. the congressional district delegates are chosen in caucuses within 60 days of the primary. the at-large delegates are selected by the republican state committee within 45 days of the congressional district caucuses
