nevada republicans use a three-step system of caucuses and conventions to pick their national convention delegates
the process begins with precinct caucuses scheduled for feb. 18. a straw poll of presidential preference is conducted at the county caucuses, but participants are not bound to presidential candidates
the county conventions, which are held in march, elect delegates to the state convention
national convention delegates are elected at the state convention
