palestinians stabbed to death an arab policeman suspected of aiding israel and wrapped his body in a palestinian flag, and another arab was killed today by israeli gunfire, hospital officials and witnesses said
the suspected collaborator was slain in a refugee camp near jericho, the reports said, the second killing of a suspected collaborator in the occupied territories since palestinian unrest began dec. 8
the army confirmed that the body of nabil juma farah, 30, had been found in the aqbat jaber refugee camp, but said it was investigating the cause of his death
according to u.n. figures, 83 arabs have been killed by israelis since the riots began in the lands israel captured during the 1967 middle east war
elsewhere in the west bank, doctors said three male protesters were wounded today by israeli gunfire and arab women heeded underground calls to demonstrate
also today, the military said four army officers who were unarmed when three plo guerrillas commandeered their car and went on to hijack a bus monday were sentenced to 35 days in jail for not carrying weapons
