a man who claims he was bitten by a black widow spider during a church bingo game has sued the church
kevin w. leonard is suing holy spirit catholic church for $1,004.91 in medical bills, $67 in lost wages and an unspecified amount for physical pain and mental anguish
leonard said he was bitten on the lower leg as he sat at a bingo table last june. a doctor later diagnosed the bite as having come from a black widow spider, according to matt parmenter, leonard's attorney
the spider's venom can affect the central nervous system, although it is generally not fatal to adults
the suit claims negligence on the part of the church and the diocese
the rev. patrick foster, pastor of holy spirit, declined to comment on the suit, filed friday in vanderburgh superior court
