that settlement is woefully inadequate,'' said ronald d. krist, a houston attorney who represented astronauts' survivors from the apollo spacecraft fire in 1967 as well as three families from the 1986 space shuttle disaster
krist said the four challenger families in the government-company settlement should have and ``would have netted more money'' if they had hired lawyers. news digest: undated _ sup--elections rdp; undated _ sup--democrats; undated _ sup--republicans; chicago _ sup--on to illinois; undated sup--state primaries rdp; panama city, panama _ panama; washington _ challenger settlement; dedham, mass. _ ritalin irony.</note>
